definitions.definition: An installation : the process of installing a software application.
examples: The install takes a long time, but you can run it in the background while working on other things.

definitions.definition: An installation: a software application that has been installed.
examples: I've customized my local install ; the out-of-the-box version looks a bit different.

main_definition: ( computing , informal ) An installation : the process of installing a software application.
secondary_definitions: ( computing , informal ) An installation: a software application that has been installed.
